  <original-body>Sometimes want to update a counter that hasn't a default value, therefore nil (null in the database) is the default.

With this patch update_counters will work on null values assuming they have a value of 0.

Also added a method to connection adapters to achieve this without doing additional queries, the if_null method. In postgres sub-queries will be necessary since there is no IF or IFNULL function out of the box.

Tested in mysql, sqlite, sqlite3 and postgres.</original-body>
